string-array.item: Q.1 P is Q’s brother, R is Q’s mother, S is R’s father, T is S’s mother. What is the relation of P with T?
Q.2 A is a mother of B, C is a son of A, D is a brother of E, E is a daughter of B, B is a brother of F, then D is a grandmother of –
Q.3 X is Y’s brother, Y is Z’s wife, Z is W’s son, W is V’s wife. What is the relation of V with Y ?
Q.4 A and B are sister, R and S are brothers, daughter of A is sister of R, then what is the relation of B with S?
Q.5 A said to B: “C is my father’s nephew. D is my uncle\' child, but not C’s brother.’’ What is the relation of D with C?
Q.6 E is a sister of B, A is a father of C, B is a son of C, then what is the relation of A with E?
Q.7 A man pointed a photograph and said to his friend: “She is the daughter of the only son of my father’s wife.’’ How the girl in the photograph is related to that person?
Q.8 A is a brother of B, C is father of D, E is a mother of B, A and D are brother, then what is the relation of E with C?
Q.9 ‘A’ is a brother of ‘B’ and ‘C’. ‘D’ is mother of ‘C’. ‘E’ is father of ‘A’, then which of the following is definitely not true?
Q.10 A is son of B, B and C are sisters, E is a mother of C, If D is a son of E, then which of the following statements is true?
Q.11 A woman introduced a boy and said: “His uncle (mama) and my uncle(mama) are brother of each other.’’ What is the relation of the woman with that boy?
Q.12 Vinod pointed Archana and told: “Her father is a son of my mother’s sister.’’ What is the relation of Archana with Vinod?
Q.13 C is nephew of A’s father. D is A’s cousin, but not C’s brother. How D is related to C?
Q.14 Mihir shows a picture and says: “His/her sister is a mother of my brother’s son Tushar.’’ How Mihir is related to Tushar?
Q.15 Juhi pointed Sanjay and said: “He is the husband of the only sister of my father’s wife’s son.’’ How Juhi is related to Sanjay?
Q.16 A man introduced a woman and told : “Her mother’s husband’s sister is my aunt (mousi).’’ What is the relation of that woman with the man?
Q.17 My mother showed me a photograph and said: “This beautiful lady’s husband is a son of your mother.’’ If I have not any brother, then what is my relation with the lady in photograph?
Q.18 Ravi pointed a picture of a girl and said: “Her mother’s brother is the only son of my mother’s father.’’ What is the relation of girl’s mother with Ravi?
Q.19 A is B’s daughter, B is C’s mother, D is C’s brother. What is the relation of D with A?
Q.20 A person introduced a lady and said "She is samdhan of the mother-in-law of the only daughter-in-law of my son’s grandmother." How that person is related to the lady?
Q.21 A is the son of B.C, B`s sister has a son D and a daughter E.F is the maternal uncle of D. How is E related to F?
Q.22 Rahul`s mother is the only daughter of Monika`s father. How is Monika`s husband related to Rahul?
Q.23 A is the son of B. C, B`s sister has a son D and a daughter E. F is the maternal uncle of D. How is A related to D?
Q.24 Q`s mother is sister of P and daughter of M. S is daughter of P and sister of T. How is M related to T?
Q.25 Deepak is brother of Ravi. Rekha is sister of Atul. Ravi is son of Rekha. How is Deepak related to Rekha?

Q.11 In a certain code language, ‘123’ means ‘bright little boy’, ‘145’ means ‘tall big boy’ and ‘637’ means ‘beautiful little flower’. Which digit in that language means ‘bright’?

Q.12 In a certain language ‘go for morning walk’ is written as ‘$*?#’, ‘good for health’ is written as ‘£?@’ and ‘good to walk fast’ is written as ‘+@↑#’, then what is the code for ‘health’ in that code language?
Q.13 In a certain code language ‘Pen pencil’ is written as ‘$£’, ‘eraser sharpener’ is written as ‘@#’ and ‘pencil eraser’ is written ‘$@’. Then, what is the code for ‘pen’ ?
Q.14 In a certain code, ‘786’ means ‘study very hard’ ‘958’ means ‘hard work pays’ and ‘645’ means ‘study and work’. Which of the following is the code for ‘very’?
Q.15 In a certain code language ‘123’ means ‘hot filtered coffee’. ‘356’ means ‘very hot day’ and ‘589’ means ‘day and night’. Which digit stands for ‘very’?
Q.16 In a certain code language, ‘234’ means ‘spark and fire’, ‘456’ means ‘spark is cause’ and ‘258’ means ‘fire is effect’. Which of the following numerals is used for ‘cause’?
Q.17 In a certain code language, ‘253’ means ‘book are old’, ‘546’ means ‘man’ is old’ and ‘378’ means ‘buy good books’. What stands for ‘are’ in that code ?
Q.18 In a certain code, ‘467’ means ‘leaves are green’, ‘485’ means ‘green is good’ and ‘639’ means ‘they are playing’. Which digit stands for ‘leaves’ in that code?
Q.19 In a certain code language, ‘134’ means ‘good and tasty’, ‘478’ means ‘see good pictures’ and ‘729’ means ‘picture are faint’. Which of the following digits stands for ‘see’?

Q.20 In a certain code language ‘3a, 2b, 7c’ means ‘truth is eternal’; ‘7c, 9a, 8b, 3a’ means ‘enmity is not eternal’ and ‘9a, 4d, 2b, 8b’ means ‘truth does not perish’. Which of the following means ‘enmity’ in that language?
